    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Clay capable of withstanding very high termperatures without fusing or softening; used especially for firebrick and crucibles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Arcilla capaz de soportar temperaturas muy elevadas sin fundirse ni ablandarse, utilizada en especial en ladrillos de hornos y crisoles.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
